description:
The collected issues, 1-5, of the storyline "The Trap."

In the small town of Heaven's Gate hides a dark secret inside the old Thomas farm house. A group of laborers venture inside and are horribly murdered one by one, leaving the last few to discover a ravenous and cunning monster.
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Stillborn: The First Zombie: The Trap

description:
The creative team of Patrick Gerard and Eryck Webb (TRANSFORMERS COLLECTOR'S CLUB MAGAZINE) team up for a critically acclaimed reconstructionist super-hero adventure about a hero and his polar bear friend, joined by established comics veterans like Brian Augustyn (BATMAN: GOTHAM BY GASLIGHT), Tom Peyer (HOURMAN), Art Thibert (THE NEW 52: FUTURES END), and James Ritchey III (THE GREEN LAMA). The book also features fresh talent such as Armand Villavert (GLADSTONE'S SCHOOL FOR WORLD CONQUERORS), John Derrick West (IMAGINARY DRUGS).

This volume collects UNGROUNDED #1-8.

Storytellers

Wicker: Storytellers is a collection of shorts, featuring a plethora of talented artists, each digging deeper inside the characters of Wicker.

This issue contains 5 stories, focusing on love, madness, sacrifice, loneliness, and one starring Steve Benton's "American Bison", in a crossover with the Wicker Witch herself! Artists include Ken Lamug, Ed Bickford, Saint Yak, Kris Harris, Mir Ubetri, and Rob Cannon, making this offering a great addition for any comic-lovers and wicker-fans alike!

The story so far....

The Blacksheep crew is trying to figure out where to go next, meanwhile on earth in the milkyway galaxy, Joran is preparing the remaining citizens to evacuate to the core worlds in order to keep peace with the Hulduvian Empire. The agreement is to let the Hulduvian Empire have the outer rim of the galaxy.

Infection

After barely escaping their own undead fans, the Subliminal Torment crew return to their hunt for Diablo's Scorn. But on their way they invoke the wrath of a group of creatures thought only to exist in urban legends- "The Albinos!"
name: Infection

description:
Then And Now

As the Briathos continue to battle the forces of an multi-dimensional being we take a peak into the past to see how it all began.
name: Then And Now

description: Drugged and institutionalised, Lucy is tormented by the memory of her dead son, Cale, and the fear of losing baby Alex to the authorities. Now a patient of Roch House, she's about to meet the other residents of this creepy establishment and discover the real motivations behind the Divine Order of God.
name: Chapter 2

description: After the exciting festivities of the Japanese new year, Sister Long has one of the hardest months of her mission so far. Dealing with a new companion, the bitter cold of winter, and having few people to teach takes its toll.
name: Month 12: January

volume.name: DENDO: One Year and One Half in Tokyo

description:
From the Somewhat Secret Files of... Fisherman!

When hordes of amateur unschooled ninjas plan to attack the city, fierce anti-hero 'Fisherman' need help! So, He calls upon the assistance of The Disgruntled Avenger to save the city!
name: From the Somewhat Secret Files of... Fisherman!

description: Hope you're hungry! Pull up a chair and get ready for a delicious stack of hot cakes, smothered in syrup, with a side of crispy bacon, and a heaping helping of alien intrigue!

With Tamai destroyed a shaman turtle unearths a strange secret among the ruins as things look down for Bones. Could the discovery of a traitor be the end of our intrepid crew? There's only one way to find out! Okay, two; you could wait to see if we're in next month's PREVIEWS, but why would you gamble and miss this awesome book?

When the Moment Comes

Something terrible is pushing it's way into our reality. The only thing standing in it's way, are a group of newly activated heroes with no training whatsoever!
name: When the Moment Comes

description: Picking up threads from issue #1, the first arc concludes with a bang. Secrets are revealed and unlikely alliances formed, all while the world marches unwittingly toward its own demise.

Kitsune: Assassin For Hire is an adult comic series for mature readers and follows the exploits of a female assassin in the pre-modern Japan era.

In the second issue, the assassin, Kitsune, ventures into a nearby town after assassinating a Daimyo of the neighbouring province. By coincidence, she runs into an old face from her past. Meanwhile, the Shogun, supreme military ruler of the land, is none too pleased that a Daimyo is assassinated under his watch...

An Electric Moon

An unconventional romance is threatened by the latest innovation -- electric light!

Broken Sky

Next Town Over's seventh chapter, in which Black and Hunter make their way to frontier metropolis and geological wonder Broken Sky.
name: Broken Sky

description: Anansi introduces Richard to Ernie, the used god salesman, but a spacial shift leads them into a confrontation with the Dream Eaters.

Night Of The Wolves

7 months after the events of "Brothers Out of Bond", Khenti & Nekhet are enjoying their new Powers as the heads of a powerful Werewolf gang called the Jackals in the Egyptian Port City of Aswan. Raiding Royal Caravans and living large, they plan one final score before they head to Nubia as planned...

The Pack is a Graphic Novel following a pack of African Werewolves. It follows their tales and misadventures as they travel through the fantasy land of Aya…
name: Night Of The Wolves

description: Issue #7 will see the war between Penguins and Possums escalating to a fever pitch. The pieces of the final battle are in place, and all of humanity will be caught in the crossfire!

Jailbreak

As The Sheriff continues to put pressure on John to turn himself in, Rob and his band attempt a daring rescue of John's father from prison.
name: Jailbreak

volume.name: Robin Hood: Outlaw of the 21st Century

description:
and the Mountain of the White Death

Sebastian Hawks, self-proclaimed Creature Hunter, has been labeled a scourge of natural science. His claims of the existence of mythical beasts have resulted in little more than ridicule and a tarnished reputation.

But when Hawks is approached by an agent of the crown to hunt 'beings' that threaten the British Empire, he thrusts himself headlong into danger. Can Sebastian and his trusted batman, Benoit, overcome the terror they encounter on the mountain of the white death?
name: And the Mountain of the White Death

description:
Chapter 19

Jeff's soccer trip falls on a full moon. Connor agrees to help cover for him and excited to introduce Jeff to his boyfriend.
name: Chapter 19

description: Written, drawn, printed, collated, folded, and stapled the DIY way: self-published and self-distributed mini comics revolutionized the medium. A subculture that thrives and depends on selling and trading these handcrafted booklets, there are no barriers of entry, no profiteering, and no cookie-cutter normalcy; the only limits are what the hand can draw. For more than 40 years, these tiny tomes have been fueling the alternative comics scene, and the Treasury of Mini Comics Volume 2 continues the historical survey of the world's smallest comics from some of today's biggest names.
name: Volume Two

description:
The Urban Myth Investigators are back!

Issue three picks up shortly after issue two, and Earl The Gnome has taken a weekend vacation trip back home. But when Chupie and Steve accidentally stumble into his living room, it isn't long before mystery and intrigue ensue. A gnome village, the kaleidoscope windmill, and the midnight forest where unbeknownst to everyone, The Frogs have taken residence.

City Of Heroes

On the way back from a mission the members of chess Strike Team encounter epic battle going on in the city between an invasion of robots and a superhero team better known as The Guild. Seeing the Guild losing their advantage the members of Chess decide to use their strategic expertise to help out. Joining into the battle. As the two teams worked together on an uneasy Alliance. They stop The Invasion and save the city.
name: City Of Heroes

description: After a bad day at school, Kyrda Franks mouths off to a reporter. Things go a little off the rails from there.

A graphic novel collection of the gay comic series featuring bittersweet adventures in gay dating, complicated soap-opera relationships, dating and tricking mishaps. Lots of fun and games. Volume 3 collects issues 7, 8, and 9 of the series, plus exclusive material and a story done for the Prism Comics annual guide to LGBT comics.

Will Tighe recover from his comeuppance? Who is Warren's freaky stalker? With Micah out of the picture, will Eric fall for Sam... or someone else?
name: Vol. 3

description:
The first volume of The Happiness Agent collects the first four chapters into one big download! 106 HD pages brings us through the first story arc.

In the not-too-distant future, displays are captured on glasses and contacts. Implants allow people to control their pocket computers through thought. Memories are stored and can be reviewed. Up until now, though, no one has been able to modify them.

Lorelai has broken that code, and with it is trying to improve people's lives by altering their bad memories. But such knowledge cannot go unnoticed, and such a well-meaning act can have far reaching consequences for everyone involved.
name: Vol. 1

description:
Inky Equation:

Old School being Renovated (+) Haunted Past (X) Magic, Mystery & Mayhem (-) Adult Supervision = (Trouble & Fun in Every Adventure)!

Plot:

Inky is a young boy with a very active imagination and a group of friends who enjoy getting into trouble as much as he does. Inky and his friends attend a very old middle school with an alleged haunted past, which is presently being renovated. While exploring the basement of the old school, Inky and his friends find a very unusual eraser hidden in the walls. Inky soon learns that it is no ordinary eraser—it possesses the power to open a gateway into the past, future & unknown worlds! Classroom to classroom Inky and his friends open this gateway and explore the mysteries and adventures of various times and places with the powers of this very mysterious and Magical Eraser.

Imagine the possibilities!

Nicole J. Georges captures her adventures and thoughts in unique, heartfelt illustrations & stories. Five years of dog mothering, chicken raising, coffee-shop crushes, drama, low paying jobs, heartbreaking romance, inspiring friendships, vegan snacks, & more! This collection will take the reader on a whirlwind tour through Nicole's personality, wit, and charm! This second edition collects issues #1-8 of her zine and features 38 new, additional pages!
name: Vol. 1

description: They inhabited Earth longer than anyone ever knew. Today they started leaving. Today they said our world was going to end. Now our only chance for survival is some kid in Colorado who didn't know he was one of them. Until now.
name: Vol. 1

description: In this sequel to his best-selling graphic novel Maybe...Maybe Not, Ralf König tells us what happens once the honeymoon is over for newlyweds Axel and Doro and how they once again cross paths (and lock horns) with Norbert and Waltrina. Could Axel really be cheating on his pregnant wife? With another man? Ralf König's screwiest comedy yet!

Norah

Norah and her husband, Dr. James Seizhelm, were developing a drug for an intergalactic branch of the military. The drug mimicked a synthetic genome, actually altering the DNA of any subject injected with the serum. The intent was....the intent was not what happened. The result was James' death. Norah, on the other hand, took the drug without any immediate adverse side effects. Norah and her sister, Vera, would go on to save the world, but that's a different story.

This is after that time.

Today, she is making a living as a coma-fisher; one who pulls people from their comatose state. She helps families all over the country retrieve the souls of their loved ones. This particular evening, Norah finds herself at the Massachusetts General Hospital in Boston. She took the case of 5-year-old Anna, who suffered a seizure that caused her to bash her head against a tub. Her parents have hired Norah to come and fish her from the coma before she slips away into death.

In Chapter One...

meet a young boy, alone in a barren land on a search for food. Guided by an unknown voice, he ventures into the city, long abandoned by mankind for fear of the walking death.

During a huge flood, ERIC BLOCK receives DEATH's unexpected visit, who gives him seven days of immortal life to solve his problems and to avenge the death of his daughter Aurora. After the seven days, DEATH will take ERIC with her, forever.

ERIC's daughter Aurora was killed by the private police during a demonstration agains a huge oil and gas corporation called the Pacific Edge.

So ERIC starts climbing the mountain of vengeance to the top where the true responsible people of Aurora's death and the destruction of Eric's life are.

SILENCE OF GOD

Deep beneath the heart of Texas it lies: the Supercollider, the world's largest, most powerful particle accelerator. But a horrific disaster in the mid-'80s left it highly radioactive, killing everyone including the project's head scientist, Dr. William Erie.

Now, twenty years later, Sara Erie--the doctor's daughter --is determined to find out the real story. But when Sara and an investigative team descend into the Supercollider, they find no bodies--just abandoned radiation badges. Shadowy, inhuman figures that move very fast, keeping out of sight in the darkened tunnels. Frogs frozen in an amber-like substance. And one word, scrawled repeatedly on the walls in blood:

PARA

What does it mean? The answer may spell the key to the Universe's origins--or to its end.

Laws of Men: part one.

Stranded on a road they shouldn't be on, no sooner than returning to Elutheria, Eboni and Bolo find themselves caught in the crossfire of warring political factions.

Maddie, following the orders of her matriarch looks for her perfect opportunity to complete her mission.

Pick up the story from where the prologues left off as "The Sword is my Lady. The Lady is my Sword." kicks off it's first arc "Laws of Men."
name: Part One

volume.name: The Sword Is My Lady. The Lady Is My Sword.: Laws of Men

description:
New York

The year is 1996. The daughter of a celebrated superheroic duo awakens from a two-year coma in a mysterious facility with no memory of what happened to her. As she struggles to remember the horrific tragedy that put her there and killed scores Earth's greatest heroes, clandestine forces weigh the value of her life as their secret plans unfold. So begins The Uniques - a story of powerful young people coming of age in a world where the super is common but heroes are not.
name: New York
The Spirit's own purposeful guide to clean living
Auf der Suche nach dem verlorenen Freund

description:
Coups? Phantoms? Alibi Jones: Magnet for Trouble!

Alibi Jones - mediator for The Solar Alliance Interplanetary Force - The SAIF - in the 2130s - negotiates agreements between humans, humankind and alien races. He's the foster son of the former leader of the Solar Alliance. And he seems to have a knack for being in interesting places at most interesting times! Featuring two stories:

"Alibi Jones: Vacation" - After rescuing his now-girlfriend Katie from alien kidnappers (a story told in the novel ALIBI JONES), Alibi decides he and Katie need a vacation. They set out to visit their Dakhur friend Kit at his new diplomatic job on the planet called "Paradise" - not knowing a coup is about to erupt! Leave it to Alibi to get caught in the middle of EVERYTHING!

-and-

"Alibi Jones & the Wishing Stone" - When Finder (whom Alibi met in the novel ALIBI JONES AND THE SUNRISE OF HUR) sends Alibi off to find an old alien relic known as the "Wishing Stone", Alibi discovers being careful what you wish for isn't merely an old cliche!

The Escapades Of Air Raid Robertson

Comicdom's favorite quixotic aviator returns with three more adventures. They include...

"Way Out West" - Mara is a middle-class office worker who lives a normal life. So, why does she become the focal point of a daring heist perpetrated by The Burple Bopper? Does Air Raid Robertson know?

"Toccata & Fugue" - Air Raid Robertson and Ridley investigate a cold case regarding a series of killings that occurred in an opera house. The trail leads to a so-called "Angel Of Music".

"Out Ta Get Me" - The zombie of Krull-Gor The Mighty is causing trouble in a subterranean world populated by dinosaur people. The mysterious Fantomah isn't exactly thrilled with the idea of calling in Air Raid Robertson for help, but circumstances give her little choice in the matter.
name: Way Out West; Toccata & Fugue; Out Ta Get Me

description:
Outbreak

Subliminal Torment and Diablo's Scorn finally come together to settle their grievances with each other in the most violent ways available! Questions are answered and new secrets are revealed within this stunning conclusion.
name: Outbreak

description:
Rebellious Youth.

Still reeling from the revelation his adopted daughter has joined the resistance, the Commander finds himself deep underneath the city of Moscow desperately trying to save her from an unknown enemy.
name: Rebellious Youth.

description:
Book Two: Come as you are.

The bloodthirsty cult begins its sacrificial ritual in the hopes of gaining immortality even as Sara is released from prison.
name: Book Two: Come As You Are.

description:
The Cruel Dance Music of the Universe -Part 4

Surrounded by 3-eyed Purple monkeys from another dimension and like, totally out of options... Bob makes a phone call to Mr. Medusa, former intergalactic hitman (...and currently living with Bob's parents.) in a desperate plea for help.

Can Mr. Medusa save him?
name: The Cruel Dance Music of the Universe - Part 4

story_arc_credits.name: The Cruel Dance Music of the Universe

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: The Cruel Dance Music of the Universe

description:
School of Villainy: Bad Hair Day

The Nefarious Nerd is back and he's built his evil lair right next to Dylan's. Dylan McVillain and Eugene the Robot are going to find themselves in a hairy situation when they confront the Nefarious Nerd.
name: School of Villainy: Bad Hair Day

description:
The Fourth and Final issue of The Gamma Gals: Zero G!

The girls are faced with a difficult battle, as Zero G's actions have catastrophic ramifications for the people of Brightstone, and their super-powered protectors!

Moeketsi

After the bold wetwork heist in Issue 05 exposes Floria Dorazio's nefarious activities, Splitfin head of security, Kippie Moeketsi, has to work on serious damage control. Meanwhile, Hex Spencer is introduced to Rada Raja at Ganesa Dispatch. The Gatecrashing garage.
name: Moeketsi

description: Happy Hour in America is cartoonist Tim Lane's one-man, self-published anthology consisting o fnew short stories, selected material from three new books in progress, and other experimental work.
Happy Hour in America is cartoonist Tim Lane's one-man, self-published anthology consisting o fnew short stories, selected material from three new books in progress, and other experimental work.

Wine and Vines part 3 of 3

From hoedown to showdown! it's a kayak hijack! a swampy stompy! It's a rumble in the...well you get the point.
name: Wine and Vines Part 3 of 3

description:
Buzzkill

Paddy and Chester stumble upon a cafe filled with beautiful women who absolutely adore them. Wait. That can't be right, can it? Cupid certainly doesn't think so.
name: Buzzkill

description:
Escape

The walking skeleton walks into a difficult situation, then takes desperate measures.
name: Escape

description:
The noise of thunder, part fourteen.

Attikus and Zudhra, Tessa's parents, have regained their original bodies and powers, and they surely don't look and act like their previous Community personas! Problem is, like every member of the Community and Jill, they're under the Artisan's control. Will their parental love be enough to set them free? Meanwhile, Thunder Girl and Dawnchild are working on a way to bring Tessa back, and Balthazaar makes his move.
name: The Noise of Thunder, Part Fourteen

description:
The Secret History of the 20th Century

Did the red planet cause the Red Scare? Plus, the silent "Cargo Cult" takes us to ancient Egypt!
name: The Secret History of the 20th Century

description:
On the Road

A stormy night in 1964. Ken Kesey and the Merry Pranksters stop the Furthur bus to pick up a hitchhiker, a mysterious old man named Art Waters. When they give him LSD, they unlock his memories... and things get weird...
name: On the Road

description:
On the Bus

Enter Charlie Many Colors, a Hopi/Comanche medicine man and US Army vet, who has just escaped from San Quentin. Meanwhile, the more stories that Art Waters tells, and the more his mind opens under powerful psychedelics, the more visible he becomes to old enemies in another dimension...
name: On the Bus

description:
Empire State

The forces of Shadow are tracking Charlie Many Colors in the hope that he will lead them to Art Waters. But Art is many miles away in New York on a psychedelic journey with Allen Ginsburg and Timothy Leary...
name: Empire State

description:
Eternal Return

Art and Charlie barely escape the Veil, but by recovering precious memories they are one step closer to unlocking the key to the legendary Chronicles of Akasha. Little do they know, a contract has just been taken out on their lives. Beware the Fisher!
name: Eternal Return

description:
Initiation

To help Art recover still missing pieces of his spirit, Charlie Many Colors leads him in a peyote ceremony -- back into the past, back to their childhood together and the initiation that Wandering Eye gave them...
name: Initiation

description:
War Stories

The forces of Shadow finally catch up to Art and Charlie -- and an epic battle ensues. The psychedelic journey continues with Art remembering his service with MK-ULTRA and the artifact that would change the outcome of the war...
name: War Stories

description:
Empyrean

The occult warriors Art Waters and Charlie Many Colors go on a top-secret mission after the war -- only to be blown again into the "infinite moment." This time it leads to the cosmic dimension of the Empyrean, and much is revealed...
name: Empyrean

description:
Keepin' Em Out Of Jail

An epic battle-featuring monsters, robots, and cops-is about to make the jailhouse rock!

A bullet-proof, robot-armed sheriff must protect the local prison from a siege of zombies out to destroy his deputy daughter, who's not bullet-proof in the slightest. Add a werewolf, a voodoo priestess, and demon spiders, and the jail just overflows with stuff that's monstrous...

This lightning-paced one-shot from Source Point Press delivers chills and laughs for monster-lovers from age 9 to 999.
name: Keepin' Em Out Of Jail

description:
Chapter 5 of 8: Lucifer's daemons come home to roost

Before he was the Devil, He was Lucifer Morningstar. Brightest of all the Archangels, Marshall of Heaven. This is the story of his Fall.

The Man in White

Ed must walk a fine line in order to not be discovered as the vigilante. Due to his crusade, the mob has brought in a high class assassin to kill him.
name: The Man in White

description:
Several tales feature women wronged seeking the ultimate revenge, empowered by the spirit of Lady Justice. In "Control Freak," Brigitte Diamond (formerly Brigitte Dyson) is on a quest for justice that leads her to the man who taught her to kill-her lover! It's steel against steel as she fights the final battle for her sanity and her soul. "Woman About Town" features two ex-cons with a new score planned-but there's betrayal in the air. When the smoke clears, there's going to be a price to be paid, and the new Lady Justice will be there to collect it. Plus: Slow Death," "Disliked and Feared," and the origin of Lady Justice is finally revealed in "The Highest Bidder."

Note: The digital edition (5/11/2016) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Volume Two

description:
The award-nominated UK superhero soap opera series continues!

The O Men have captured one of their biggest enemies, and now they want answers. What makes her tick? Why is she so evil? And how are other O Men characters involved in her past?

Get ready for a shocking origin story with a difference in the epic 'Trials'.

New Friends, new Foes.

Creeo continues his infiltration of a technologically inferior planet filled with orcs and sword-wielding armored warriors in the hopes of exploiting the world's natural resources.
name: New Friends, New Foes.

volume.name: On the Brink of the Universe

description:
Time Loop

Tallulah is trapped in a time loop and living the same stupid day over and over and over and OVER. Sanity can usually fix this sort of thing with science, but will she be able to find a solution when she keeps forgetting everything she's already tried each time the day resets?
name: Time Loop

volume.name: Sanity & Tallulah: Plucky Teen Girl Space Detectives

description:
What are dreams made of?

...We have no idea, but in this issue of Task Force Rad Squad, Red Fighter's friends rush to rescue him from the menace of Multi-Monst!

Splashback

That Guy deals with the fallout of the Ventura killing, we get to see a new issue of NutSac, the Jimmy Piss broadshow live on TV, plus all the usual violence and tits.
name: Splashback

description: In the aftermath of Hurricane Katrina, a centuries old family curse is reignited by an undead voodoo priest. When paranormal researcher Alfred Carter is summoned by the ghost of his ancestor, he must travel to The Big Easy to cleanse his bloodline. What he finds are untold family secrets and a descent into madness. Alred learns more of his family's cursed past and how his great, great grandfather, Maximillian Carter had come to be a practitioner of the dark arts. Also revealed is how Laveau became an undead Voodoo priest. This disturbing tale can be described as H.P. Lovecraft meets Angel Heart.

Society has broken down. Chaotic, bloody violence sweeps the streets and the Government is powerless to act.

Meanwhile overseas, KingSword heads a desperate gambit to bring home as many troops as possible while back home, the other half of the team tackle a trio of ruthless, super-powered assassins.

With time running out for our heroes, can they rally their might against the hordes of enemies that converge on Downing Street for a final, apocalyptic showdown?

Find out in VANGUARD - issue seven!

The Chant and the Aardvark

Joined by a team of The Tick, Gumby & Pokey, Bone, Flaming Carrot, Felix the Cat, Milk & Cheese, Rat Bastard, Reid Fleming, Usagi Yojimbo, Mr. Spook, Zippy the Pinhead, Toxie, Protoplasman and Too Much Coffee Man, our hero Cerebus looks for his helmet, only to find it in the hands of Public Enemy!

List of covers and their creators:

CoverNameCreator(s)Sidebar Location
RegRegular CoverDon Simpson1
RegFlip CoverRick Parker2
name: --I Get My Hair Cut This Wayyyy!!!

description:
Clancy Wallencheck is a very bad man - the commander of an elite team that have nothing to live for and a whole lot of people to kill.

From the mountains of Pakistan to the waters of Venice, there have been a thousand corpses in Clancy's life.

This is the story of the one that mattered.

SLIME has dominated Terror Alliance Pro Wrestling for almost 20 years. Their reign of destruction goes unchallenged, but a new challenger may answer the call. But it will take more than a fighting spirit to become the Interzone Ultimo Elite Worlds Heavyweight Championship belt.

As Stella Kim’s journey into the Chaos Arena of Crystal Fighters continues, she’ll face down the deadly duo of Bit and Digit. Will Stella’s overconfidence get the better of her, or can she continue to rise through the ranks of the underground magical girl fight club?

After Stella Kim’s incredible introduction to the Chaos Arena hidden deep in the code of the Crystal Fighters MMO, it’s time for her to level up with a new mentor. But will her new training be enough to defeat another duo with powers that go beyond Stella’s imagination?

Brandon has a seemingly perfect life. Model by day and indulging in all the parties at night. But under the surface, Brandon hides his terrible past...one that he believes he has paid insufficient penance. But as he sees it there is a way out of this predicament and that means he is coming for you, sinners. Part one of two. From writer Matt Nicholls (Collateral) and artist Simon Wright (Zombie Cities).

A group of time travellers return to the start of the Consortium to eliminate a major figure from history.

What effect will it have?

volume.name: Era: The Consortium - Counting Down From One

description: A group of Resistance fighters attempt to foil a plot which will otherwise cost 14 billion lives!

volume.name: Era: The Consortium - The Last Stand of Stiletto Unit

description:
The Hard Hello

Chain-smoking, alcoholic and foul-mouthed Sid the Squirrel is in for a big surprise while investigating a homicide. Everything is about to change for the Squirrel Detective, and for Animanhattan.
name: The Hard Hello

description: A mysterious magician searches the Weird West for the elusive Dr. Death.
